Setup the raspberry pi3b as an digital audio converter
======================================================

Goal: stream USB audiointerface (BOOM) to hifiberry digi+ on s/pdif coax

. disable [comment] onboard audio
  # cd /boot
  # vi config.txt
    #dtparam=audio=on
    dtparam=audio=off

. activate the hifiberry digi+
  # cd /boot
  # vi config.txt
    dtoverlay=hifiberry-digi
  # reboot
  
. list audio devices
  # arecord -L
  # aplay -L
  - for BOOM use:
    HW:CARD=BOOM,DEV=0
  - for digi+ use:
    plughw:CARD=sndrpihifiberry,DEV=0

. create scripts for alsaloop:
/usr/bin/alsaloop \
  -v \
  -C hw:CARD=BOOM,DEV=0 \
  -P plughw:CARD=sndrpihifiberry,DEV=0 \
  -f S32_LE \
  -r 48000 \
  -c 2 \
  -l 1024
  -t 20000 \
  -S

. run it
